      "writtenOn": "2021-01-15T01:44:36Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Yes, I can take on the rebaselining work forward if/when this becomes the default.  (I\u0027d probably need help w/Skia Gold, though.)\n\nI just tried a full run_web_test pass on my Dev box, and the results were actually better than I feared... out of 98k tests, there were 567 regressions.  \n\nScanning through the results, I think a good number of the \"regressions\" are due to different fonts on my system vs. the test VMs (and sampling a few shows the same failure with the feature turned off), so the *real* number of failures is probably considerably lower than that.\n\nAll the tests under `virtual/text-antialias` suite failed, as was to be expected.\n\nIMO, this seems like a manageable set of failures to rebaseline.\n\n(I\u0027ve not run any \u0027experiments\u0027 before, so any advice on percentages/rollout-plan are appreciated.)",
      "parentUuid": "0cb7ca27_bc429a7d",
      "revId": "e1cf5a1b7b2ef43c5fba326aabdd8f04de8f9027",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02"
    },
